<!--
  This file is a placeholder pointer for the Detekt baseline.

  Detekt does not natively merge baselines across multi-module Gradle builds:
  each module owns its own baseline file written by `./gradlew detektBaseline`.
  We keep all of them in this directory under `baseline-<module>.xml` and
  reference them from each module's `detekt { baseline = ... }` block.

  See:
    - build.gradle.kts (root)               -> subprojects { detekt { baseline = .../baseline-$name.xml } }
    - fixthis-gradle-plugin/build.gradle.kts -> detekt { baseline = .../baseline-fixthis-gradle-plugin.xml }

  To regenerate all baselines after intentional refactors:
    ./gradlew detektBaseline --no-daemon
    ./gradlew :fixthis-gradle-plugin:detektBaseline --no-daemon

  CI runs `./gradlew detekt --no-daemon` and fails on NEW violations only.
-->
